subSubSection.paragraph:
Setigers dorsally biannulate, weakly so on setigers 1 and 5, obscured on setigers 6–10, visible on setiger 11 and pygidium (
Figs. 7
A–B, 8A–C); anterior annulation much shorter than posterior, posterior portion of each segment with gland cells scattered across dorsum (
Fig. 7A
), similar gland cells visible on setiger 11; additional area of dark gland cells at base of parapodia (
Fig. 7A
); venter biannulate on setigers 2–5. Parapodia uniramous, mitten-shaped, shortest on setiger 1, becoming longer, rectangular in subsequent setigers; with small, translucent anterior lobe on setigers 2–3 (
Fig. 7F
), lobe decreasing in size through setiger 6, then either smaller or absent through end of body; posterior lobe lacking on all setigers; dorsal lobe small, knobby, curled dorsally, clearest on setigers 1–5/6. Dorsal cirri retained on setiger 1, otherwise absent or lost; cirri thin, smooth, filiform. Ventral cirri thin, digitate, inserted midway on parapodia. Parapodia with smooth elongate internal glands, distal end narrowing and exiting through dorsal lobe (
Fig. 7F
).
